The paper proposes a new method for exploration in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The method involves maximizing the temporal difference error, which is a key concept in reinforcement learning algorithms (cs.NE). The paper also evaluates the method on continuous control benchmark tasks, which are commonly used in robotics and control systems research (cs.RO, cs.SY).
